<li id="cite_note-Stav2003-46"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Stav2003_46-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFStav2003">Stav, Arieh (2003). "Israeli Anti-Semitism". in Sharan, Shlomo. <i>Israel and the Post-Zionists: A Nation at Risk</i>. Brighton: Sussex Academic Press. pp.&#160;171. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1903900522" class="internal">ISBN 1903900522</a>.  "Hitler simply copied Marx's own anti-Semitism."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Israeli+Anti-Semitism&amp;rft.atitle=Israel+and+the+Post-Zionists%3A+A+Nation+at+Risk&amp;rft.aulast=Stav&amp;rft.aufirst=Arieh&amp;rft.au=Stav%2C+Arieh&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B171&amp;rft.place=Brighton&amp;rft.pub=Sussex+Academic+Press&amp;rft.isbn=1903900522&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Karl_Marx"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Muravchik2003-47"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Muravchik2003_47-0" title="">^</a></b> According to Joshua Muravchik, political scientist at the <a href="/wiki/American_Enterprise_Institute_for_Public_Policy_Research" title="American Enterprise Institute for Public Policy Research" class="mw-redirect">American Enterprise Institute</a>, Marx's aspiration for "the emancipation of society from Judaism" because "the practical Jewish spirit" of "huckstering" had taken over the Christian nations is not that far from the Nazi program's twenty-four point: "combat[ing] the Jewish-materialist spirit within us and without us" in order "that our nation can […] achieve permanent health." See <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMuravchik2003"><a href="/wiki/Joshua_Muravchik" title="Joshua Muravchik">Muravchik, Joshua</a> (2003). <i>Heaven on Earth: The Rise and Fall of Socialism</i>. San Francisco: Encounter Books. pp.&#160;164. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1893554457" class="internal">ISBN 1893554457</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Heaven+on+Earth%3A+The+Rise+and+Fall+of+Socialism&amp;rft.aulast=Muravchik&amp;rft.aufirst=Joshua&amp;rft.au=Muravchik%2C+Joshua&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B164&amp;rft.place=San+Francisco&amp;rft.pub=Encounter+Books&amp;rft.isbn=1893554457&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Karl_Marx"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-48"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMaccoby2006">Maccoby, Hyam (2006). <i>Antisemitism and Modernity: Innovation and Continuity</i>. London: Routledge. pp.&#160;64–66. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/041531173X" class="internal">ISBN 041531173X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Antisemitism+and+Modernity%3A+Innovation+and+Continuity&amp;rft.aulast=Maccoby&amp;rft.aufirst=Hyam&amp;rft.au=Maccoby%2C+Hyam&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B64%E2%80%9366&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.isbn=041531173X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Karl_Marx"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
